name: tRNA (adenine22-N1)-methyltransferase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + adenine22 in tRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N1-methyladenine22 in tRNA
comment: The enzyme specifically methylates adenine22 in tRNA.

references.title: Crystal structure of Streptococcus pneumoniae Sp1610, a putative tRNA methyltransferase, in complex with S-adenosyl-L-methionine.
The YqfN protein of Bacillus subtilis is the tRNA: m1A22 methyltransferase (TrmK).
